Here are both approaches using `IQueryAttributable` on the ViewModel.

**1. Register the route** in `AppShell.xaml.cs`:

```csharp
Routing.RegisterRoute("productdetails", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
```

**2. Navigate from ProductListPage** (e.g., on CollectionView SelectionChanged):

```csharp
// Approach A — string query parameter
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"productdetails?productId={product.Id}");

// Approach B — pass the full object
var parameters = new ShellNavigationQueryParameters
{
    { "product", product }
};
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("productdetails", parameters);
```

**3. Receive on the ViewModel** — implement `IQueryAttributable` to handle both:

```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    private string _productId;
    private Product _product;

    public string ProductId
    {
        get => _productId;
        set => SetProperty(ref _productId, value);
    }

    public Product Product
    {
        get => _product;
        set => SetProperty(ref _product, value);
    }

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach A — string parameter arrives as a string value
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // Load the full product from a service, DB, etc.
        }

        // Approach B — full object arrives as-is (no serialization)
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product p)
        {
            Product = p;
            ProductId = p.Id;
        }
    }
}
```

**4. Wire the ViewModel** on `ProductDetailsPage`:

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             x:Class="MyApp.Views.ProductDetailsPage"
             x:DataType="viewmodels:ProductDetailsViewModel">
    <!-- Bind to Product or ProductId as needed -->
</ContentPage>
```

```csharp
public ProductDetailsPage(ProductDetailsViewModel vm)
{
    InitializeComponent();
    BindingContext = vm;
}
```

**Key points:**
- **String params** (`$"route?key={value}"`) — good for simple IDs; survives deep linking.
- **`ShellNavigationQueryParameters`** — passes the live object by reference; avoids re-fetching but doesn't work with URI deep links.
- Always `await` `GoToAsync` to avoid race conditions.
- `ApplyQueryAttributes` is called automatically by Shell — no manual wiring needed.
